  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>You bring up your claymore in an attempt to parry an oncoming attack and leave yourself in a more defensive stance. Make a melee Taijutsu attack at advantage against the triggering attack. If your attack result is higher than the triggering creature's, their attack misses, and all subsequent attacks are made at disadvantage.</p><p>If your attack is lower than the attack that triggered this jutsu, your AC is increased by +2 until the start of your next turn. If the result of your attack beats theirs by 5 or more, they become Dazed until the start of your next turn.</p><p><strong>At Higher Ranks:</strong> For each rank you cast this jutsu above D-Rank, increase the cost of this jutsu by 3 and the result of your attack roll by +1. If this jutsu is cast at B-Rank or higher, you may deal your weapon's damage + the difference in your attack rolls to the creature who triggered this jutsu on a success.</p>",
      "chat": ""
    },
